cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM 

This paper deals with optimizing content caching in device-to-device (D2D) communication networks, which is a subfield of wireless networking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses stochastic geometry and optimization techniques, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of Zipf distribution and small-scale fading models suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively.
